  "body": "http://doc.perl6.org/language/unicode_entry#Unicode_characters_useful_in_Perl_6\n\n“Unicode characters useful in Perl 6” – well, smartquotes are useful but are not listed yet.\n\n`‘’`, `“”`, `｢｣` – these are the basic ones, but there are other ways to write it:\n- `say ”Whoa!“`\n- `say „This works too!”`\n- `say „There are just too many ways“`\n- See [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quotation_mark#Summary_table_for_all_languages) for a bigger list.\n\nSome things to note:\n- You can nest them: `say “here: “no problem” at all!”`\n- It turns out that it is very useful in shell: `perl6 -e 'say ‘hello world’'` (that is, you can just copy some piece of code and not worry about the quotes)\n",
